  "texts": [
    "Having said that, our study is extremely compute-heavy and thus challenging to replicate on multiple LLMs: First, our fine-tuning is compute-heavy as its runs are very long as we wanted to analyze the behavior during different stages of fine-tuning (including the overfitting stages).",
    "Second, and most importantly, to facilitate our study we needed to annotate a large scale dataset w.r.t the SliCK categories.",
    "To derive reliable conclusions, it was crucial to accurately assess the model's knowledge w.r.t.",
    "a single finetuning example.",
    "In our case we run 170 inference steps per example, i.e., more than 15M inference steps to categorize our full dataset."
  ],
